metadata.name: Unholy Pope
metadata.description: Pope John XII was a historical figure who held the position of Pope in the Catholic Church from 955 to 964. He is known for his controversial actions and behavior during his papacy, including accusations of simony, murder, and adultery. Some historians have referred to him as the "Bad Pope" or the "Wicked Pope" due to his actions and reputation. However, it's important to note that the use of such terms may be subjective and controversial.
